# Taiga tickets (TJW)

When implementing a Taiga user story in `~/git`:

- Use the **taiga-ticket** skill (`~/git/tools/taiga/ticket.py` for fetch/finish — not backloggist).
- Branch: `{feat|fix|docs|chore|refactor|test|task}/TJW-###-short-slug` (infer prefix from ticket text). Honor repo `AGENTS.md` when it defines a different branch/PR flow.
- Commit messages must start with `TJW-###:`.
- One PR per modified repository; link all PRs in the Taiga comment when done.
- Prefer the repo explicitly named in the ticket (`~/git/foo`) over multi-repo exploration.
- After implementation, move the card to **Testing** unless the user specifies another column.
- Use `gh` (`~/.local/bin/gh`); if auth fails, run `python3 ~/git/tools/github/ensure_gh_auth.py`.
